      "content": "Done — I created a simple placeholder animated framing visual for `sketch-3-improve-the-agent.sk`, row `3`.\n\nWhat it shows:\n- 3 small source cards:\n  - Code + Data\n  - Foundry\n  - M365 Feedback\n- arrows converging into\n- 1 larger `Managed Agent` card\n- a small `Governance next` badge to tee up the next sketch\n\nI kept it intentionally minimal per your instruction: “simple placeholder - don't go overboard.”\n\nAlso:\n- saved the design plan first\n- saved the visual successfully\n- reviewed it\n- applied safe polish nudges (`normalize-root-layer-order`, `mark-refined`)\n\nOne note from review:\n- `Governance next` is still considered slightly small by the reviewer, but since this is a placeholder and you asked for simplicity, I left it lightweight. If you want, I can do one tiny follow-up pass to bump that label to 18px and leave everything else unchanged.",
